==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|北|肉|alt2=月|c1=p|c2=s|ls=psc|t2=meat}}. Originally written as {{lang|zh|北}}, semantic {{lang|zh|肉}} was added to be distinguished from the derived meaning of {{lang|zh|北}} (“north”).

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*bə(q)||to carry (on back), shoulder}}. According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}}, it is the [[exopassive]] of {{och-l|北|to turn one's back}} — what is turned back.

Two pronunciations were distinguished in Middle Chinese: {{m|ltc||puʌi<sup>H</sup>|t=back}}, {{m|ltc||buʌi<sup>H</sup>|t=to turn one's back to; to betray}}.

